The paper focuses on applying a novel architecture for sentiment analysis in NLP using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the adjustment of the architecture to improve feature extraction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture, which involves the use of filters, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed architecture on datasets, which is a common practice in information retrieval (cs.IR).
